04/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- The government welcomes recent reforms in Turkey designed to curb the army's influence in politics, foreign ministry spokesman Panos Beglitis said on Friday (1 August).
He added that the 7th EU reform package, which the Turkish Parliament passed last week, is another positive step towards the country's integration into the Union.
Beglitis called for the fast implementation of those reforms.
In other news Friday, the foreign ministry announced that President Costis Stephanopoulos will visit Serbia-Montenegro on 14 October.
He will participate in a Belgrade investment summit featuring chambers of commerce, business agencies and independent members of the business community from Greece, the United States and Serbia-Montenegro.
(Kathimerini - 02/08/03;
ANA, MPA - 01/08/03)
